import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Recent Changes | Policy"
  description="Stay updated on the latest changes to the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Learn about recent policy updates and how they may affect your claim.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Recent Changes to AFCS Policy</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is regularly reviewed and updated to ensure it meets the evolving needs of service personnel and veterans. This page outlines recent policy changes that may affect your claim or benefits.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">2023 Updates</h2>
        <p>Key changes implemented in 2023 include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Increased lump sum payments for certain categories of injury</li>
          <li>Extended time limits for making claims in specific circumstances</li>
          <li>Enhanced support for mental health conditions</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">2022 Policy Revisions</h2>
        <p>Significant policy changes in 2022 included:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Streamlined application process for common injuries</li>
          <li>Introduction of interim payments for complex cases</li>
          <li>Revised criteria for assessing hearing loss claims</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Mental Health Provisions</h2>
        <p>Recent years have seen a focus on improving mental health support:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Expanded list of recognised mental health conditions</li>
          <li>Improved assessment procedures for PTSD and related disorders</li>
          <li>Enhanced compensation for severe and enduring mental health issues</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Changes to Appeal Process</h2>
        <p>The appeal process has been updated to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide clearer guidance on grounds for appeal</li>
          <li>Introduce a fast-track system for certain types of appeals</li>
          <li>Enhance support for claimants during the appeal process</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Future Policy Direction</h2>
        <p>Looking ahead, potential areas for future policy development include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Further integration of AFCS with other veteran support services</li>
          <li>Exploration of new technologies for assessing and managing claims</li>
          <li>Ongoing review of compensation levels to ensure they remain appropriate</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/policy/legislation" class="text-decoration-none">AFCS Legislation</a></li>
              <li><a href="/compensation" class="text-decoration-none">Types of Compensation</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/claim-advice" class="text-decoration-none">Claim Advice</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Policy Update Webinar</h3>
            <p>Join our upcoming webinar to learn more about recent AFCS policy changes and how they might affect you.</p>
            <a href="/webinar-registration" class="btn btn-primary">Register Now</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
